quran[82]{c,v,t}:
  100,9,Do they not know that when the contents of the graves will be spilled out
  100,10,and the secrets of the hearts will be laid bareвАФ
  100,11,surely their Lord is All-Aware of them on that Day
  101,1,The Striking Disaster
  101,2,What is the Striking Disaster
  101,3,And what will make you realize what the Striking Disaster is
  101,4,ЋєIt isЋЇ the Day people will be like scattered moths
  101,5,and the mountains will be like carded wool
  101,6,So as for those whose scale is heavy Ћєwith good deedsЋЇ
  101,7,they will be in a life of bliss
  101,8,And as for those whose scale is light
  101,9,their home will be the abyss
  101,10,And what will make you realize what that is
  101,11,ЋєIt isЋЇ a scorching Fire
  102,1,Competition for more ЋєgainsЋЇ diverts you Ћєfrom GodЋЇ
  102,2,until you end up in ЋєyourЋЇ graves
  102,3,But no! You will soon come to know
  102,4,"Again, no! You will soon come to know"
  102,5,"Indeed, if you were to know Ћєyour fateЋЇ with certainty, Ћєyou would have acted differentlyЋЇ"
  102,6,ЋєButЋЇ you will surely see the Hellfire
  102,7,"Again, you will surely see it with the eye of certainty"
  102,8,"Then, on that Day, you will definitely be questioned about Ћєyour worldlyЋЇ pleasures"
  103,1,By the Ћєpassage ofЋЇ time
  103,2,Surely humanity is in ЋєgraveЋЇ loss
  103,3,"except those who have faith, do good, and urge each other to the truth, and urge each other to perseverance"
  104,1,"Woe to every backbiter, slanderer"
  104,2,who amasses wealth ЋєgreedilyЋЇ and counts it ЋєrepeatedlyЋЇ
  104,3,thinking that their wealth will make them immortal
  104,4,Not at all! Such a person will certainly be tossed into the Crusher
  104,5,And what will make you realize what the Crusher is
  104,6,ЋєIt isЋЇ GodвАЩs kindled Fire
  104,7,which rages over the hearts
  104,8,It will be sealed over them
  104,9,Ћєtightly securedЋЇ with long braces
  105,1,Have you not seen ЋєO ProphetЋЇ how your Lord dealt with the Army of the Elephant
  105,2,Did He not frustrate their scheme
  105,3,For He sent against them flocks of birds
  105,4,that pelted them with stones of baked clay
  105,5,leaving them like chewed up straw
  106,1,ЋєAt leastЋЇ for Ћєthe favour ofЋЇ making Quraysh habitually secureвАФ
  106,2,secure in their trading caravan Ћєto YemenЋЇ in the winter and ЋєSyriaЋЇ in the summerвАФ
  106,3,let them worship the Lord of this ЋєSacredЋЇ House
  106,4,Who has fed them against hunger and made them secure against fear
  107,1,Have you seen the one who denies the ЋєfinalЋЇ Judgment
  107,2,That is the one who repulses the orphan
  107,3,and does not encourage the feeding of the poor
  107,4,So woe to those ЋєhypocritesЋЇ who pray
  107,5,yet are unmindful of their prayers
  107,6,those who ЋєonlyЋЇ show off
  107,7,and refuse to give Ћєeven the simplestЋЇ aid
  108,1,"Indeed, We have granted you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ abundant goodness"
  108,2,So pray and sacrifice to your Lord ЋєaloneЋЇ
  108,3,Only the one who hates you is truly cut off Ћєfrom any goodnessЋЇ
  109,1,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬO you disbelievers"
  109,2,I do not worship what you worship
  109,3,nor do you worship what I worship
  109,4,I will never worship what you worship
  109,5,nor will you ever worship what I worship
  109,6,"You have your way, and I have my Way.вАЭ"
  110,1,When GodвАЩs ЋєultimateЋЇ help comes and the victory Ћєover Mecca is achievedЋЇ
  110,2,and you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ see the people embracing GodвАЩs Way in crowds
  110,3,"then glorify the praises of your Lord and seek His forgiveness, for certainly He is ever Accepting of Repentance"
  111,1,"May the hands of Abu Lahab perish, and he ЋєhimselfЋЇ perish"
  111,2,Neither his wealth nor ЋєworldlyЋЇ gains will benefit him
  111,3,He will burn in a flaming Fire
  111,4,"and Ћєso willЋЇ his wife, the carrier of ЋєthornyЋЇ kindling"
  111,5,around her neck will be a rope of palm-fibre
  112,1,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬHe is GodвАФOne Ћєand IndivisibleЋЇ"
  112,2,GodвАФthe Sustainer Ћєneeded by allЋЇ
  112,3,"He has never had offspring, nor was He born"
  112,4,And there is none comparable to Him.вАЭ
  113,1,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬI seek refuge in the Lord of the daybreak"
  113,2,from the evil of whatever He has created
  113,3,and from the evil of the night when it grows dark
  113,4,and from the evil of those Ћєwitches casting spells byЋЇ blowing onto knots
  113,5,and from the evil of an envier when they envy.вАЭ
  114,1,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬI seek refuge in the Lord of humankind"
  114,2,the Master of humankind
  114,3,the God of humankind
  114,4,from the evil of the lurking whispererвАФ
  114,5,who whispers into the hearts of humankindвАФ
  114,6,from among jinn and humankind.вАЭ